qas.question: What is the name of the upper house of the Marshall Islands Parliament?
Who comprises the upper house of the Marshall Islands Parliament?
How many ministers are in the Presidential Cabinet?
Along with the United Democratic Party, what party currently rules the Marshall Islands?
How many electoral districts exist in the Marshall Islands?

context: Legislative power lies with the Nitijela. The upper house of Parliament, called <a0_0>the Council of Iroij<a0_0/>, is an advisory body comprising <a1_0>twelve tribal chiefs<a1_0/>. The executive branch consists of the President and the Presidential Cabinet, which consists of <a2_0>ten<a2_0/> ministers appointed by the President with the approval of the Nitijela. The <a4_0>twenty-four<a4_0/> electoral districts into which the country is divided correspond to the inhabited islands and atolls. There are currently four political parties in the Marshall Islands: Aelon̄ Kein Ad (AKA), United People's Party (UPP), Kien Eo Am (KEA) and United Democratic Party (UDP).
